<H3> <TI>   India, Angola Agree To Cooperate on Counterterrorism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    India, Angola Agree To Cooperate on Counterterrorism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0704052794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704052794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India and Angola have agreed to cooperate at 
multilateral fora to counter the danger posed by cross-border 
terrorism and fundamentalism. The issue came up for discussion 
at the talks between the minister of state for external affairs, 
Mr. Salman Khurshid, and the minister of external relations of 
Angola, Mr. Venacio da Moura, in New Delhi today. Mr. Moura 
reiterated Angola's commitment to develop all around relations 
with India. Mr. Khurshid hoped that the current peace talks in 
Lusaka will lead to an agreement to end the internal conflict in 
Angola. 

</TEXT>

