<H3> <TI>   Constitutionality Court President Killed in Car </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Constitutionality Court President Killed in Car </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Drive-by Shooting </H4>

<F P=102> PA0204155894 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 1507 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0204155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Diego Andres de Gatica] </F>
  [Excerpt] Epaminondas Gonzalez Dubon, president of the 
Constitutionality Court and one of the country's most oustanding 
men in recent times, was killed last night. He was gunned down 
while going to his house on Seventh Ave., No. 750, Zone 2. 
Gonzalez Dubon, 64, was in a 1990 Mitsubishi white sedan with 
the license plate number 259-899 when two unidentified gunmen 
driving by in a red car shot him in the chest. 
  Gonzalez Dubon was rushed the Latinoamericano Hospital. He 
was admitted at approximately 2255, but died at 2310. Today, 
his body was taken to the Mancia Funeral Parlor in downtown 
Guatemala City, where he will be laid out and later buried. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

