<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Thwart Alleged Plan To Assassinate President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Forces Thwart Alleged Plan To Assassinate President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0504195294 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1903 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0504195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa, 5 Apr (ACAN-EFE) -- The Honduran Armed 
Forces thwarted an alleged plan which would reportedly be 
executed by three Nicaraguan citizens to assassinate President 
Carlos Roberto Reina. 
  Army Spokesman Colonel Napoleon Santos announced today 
military intelligence learned about the plan after Nicaraguan 
citizens Luis Enrique Quintero, Santiago Rivas, and Roger 
Arguello entered the country on 7 March. 
  According to the high-ranking military officer, who said 
Enrique Quintero was a member of the intelligence department of 
the Sandinist People's Army (EPS), the three Nicaraguan citizens 
had planned to burn a paint factory and kidnap three businessmen. 

</TEXT>

