<H3> <TI>   Explosion Destroys Bank Branch in Monterrey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion Destroys Bank Branch in Monterrey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0404164494 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1554 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0404164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1554 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone report by Correspondent Homero Lopez Ortiz from </F>
Monterrey -- live] 
  [Text] At 0900 this morning a strong explosion destroyed a 
branch of Banorte, located on Manuel L. Barragan and Tlalpan 
Avenues in the neighborhood of Valle de Anaguas in San Nicolas 
Uzgarte, a metropolitan municipality of Monterrey. So far, it 
has not been possible to determine the cause of the explosion. 
What was confirmed is that the building was totally destroyed 
after its personnel and some clients had already entered. The 
strong explosion also damaged some homes adjacent to the 
building. Some vehicles were also totally destroyed. Only 
license plates were left of some vehicles, which were left in 
pieces. 
  Red Cross units of San Nicolas Uzgarte Municipality, the Red 
Cross, the Green Cross, firefighters, and State Governor 
Socrates Rizo Garcia are at the scene of the tragedy. Also, 
Attorney General Benito Morales is there. State officials are 
trying to rescue the victims of the tragedy which occurred at 
0900 this morning in the Banorte branch, located on Manuel L. 
Barragan and Tlalpan Avenues in the neighborhood of Valle de 
Anaguas in San Nicolas Uzgarte in Nuevo Leon. So far it has 
been impossible to determine the number of victims. We know 
that there were some clients and personnel inside. 

</TEXT>

