<H3> <TI>   Sudanese Airliner Hijacked to Luxor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sudanese Airliner Hijacked to Luxor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604064894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0640 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Apr (MENA)--Unidentified men diverted a 
Sudanese airliner coming from Khartoum and forced its captain to 
proceed to the Luxor airport, where the airliner has landed. 
  The Boeing 737 airliner with 93 passengers and six crew 
members on board took off from Khartoum en route for 
al-Danaqilah in south Sudan. The hijacker forced the captain to 
fly to Egypt. Defense Minister Field Marshal Husayn Tantawi 
gave permission to the airliner to land at the Luxor airport. 
The hijacker is a Sudanese national and is asking for political 
asylum in Egypt. 

</TEXT>

