<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   6 April 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Airliner Takes Off for Khartoum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Airliner Takes Off for Khartoum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604153494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1455 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Luxor, 6 Apr (MENA)--The hijacked Sudanese airliner 
took off from Luxor Airport at 1600 today bound for Sudan. 
  The airliner was hijacked this morning on a domestic flight 
from Khartoum to al-Danaqilah. The Egyptian authorities and 
Armed Forces supplied the plane with fuel before it took off and 
provided food and medical care to its passengers. 
  The passengers appreciated the good hospitality they 
received 
from the Armed Forces and Egyptian officials and said it was 
nothing unusual from the fraternal and generous Egyptian people. 
  The captain of the Sudanese airliner said he would head 
first 
for al-Danaqilah and then proceed to Khartoum, adding that all 
the passengers are well. 
  A Sudanese official earlier announced that the Sudanese 
airliner left Luxor Airport two hours before it actually took 
off. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

