<H3> <TI>   Fatah, Hamas Exchange Kidnappings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah, Hamas Exchange Kidnappings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kidnaps Said Over Land Dispute </H4>

<F P=102> TA0304064294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 3 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0304064294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] A senior Fatah official was 
kidnapped by Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] activists in 
Gaza city over the weekend. Hamas claims that the man was 
collaborating with the Israeli authorities. Palestinian sources 
told our correspondent Moti Amir that the real reason behind the 
kidnapping was a dispute over land in Rafah. In the course of 
the kidnapping a violent fight broke out; one Hamas activist was 
killed and 30 were injured. The sources stressed that because 
of the continuing clashes with Hamas, Fatah was making efforts 
to capture influential positions and seize control of land and 
installations before Hamas does. 
  Our army affairs correspondent has learned that two wanted 
Hamas activists turned themselves in to the IDF over the past 
few weeks. IDF commanders in the Gaza Strip are continuing to 
hold contacts and meetings with Hamas members in an effort to 
persuade them to halt terrorist activity. Military sources said 
that the Hamas activists have a great deal of motivation to 
carry out terrorist attacks and they are expected to increase 
their efforts over the next few days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

