<H3> <TI>   APUA Head Allalou Injured in Terrorist Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    APUA Head Allalou Injured in Terrorist Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Badly Injured' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0604112194 Paris AFP in English 1101 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Algiers, April 6 (AFP) -- A prominent Algerian 
businessman and opposition party leader, Mehdi Abbas Allalou, 
was badly injured in an attack in an Algiers suburb Wednesday, 
security officials said. 
  Allalou, leader of the small Popular Association for Unity 
and Action (APUA) movement, was rushed to hospital after the 
attack in the southeastern El Harrach district. Officials gave 
no details of the circumstances. [background passage omitted] 
  The businessman, known for his close ties to the Gulf 
countries and Saudi Arabia, took a stance in favour of Kuwait 
when it was invaded by Iraq in 1991. 

</TEXT>

