<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Fire on Soldiers While `Executing Verdicts' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorists' Fire on Soldiers While `Executing Verdicts' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704203494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1950 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Suhaj, 7 Apr (MENA)--Soldier Nadi Muhammad, 20, from 
the Central Security Forces, was martyred today during a 
shoot-out in Markaz Tima in the Suhaj Governorate between a 
group from the police force and some fugitive terrorist 
elements. Terrorist 'Abd-al-Hadi Haqq was killed in the 
accident. 
  During the shoot-out, Captain Mustafa Muhammad Ahmad, 
assistant at the Markaz Tima investigations department, and 
soldier Muhammad Mutawi' received light injuries. 
  A group from the department for executing verdicts in Markaz 
Tima was executing verdicts against defendants sentenced in 
various cases. While performing its duty in Tima, the group was 
surprised by bullets directed on it by terrorists. It dealt 
with the situation immediately, killing one terrorist. The 
soldier was martyred and the Markaz Tima investigations 
assistant and another soldier were slightly injured. 
  The Suhaj Security Department command and the various 
investigation organs went to the scene to inspect it. The 
prosecution has been informed to proceed with investigations. 

</TEXT>

