  [Text] It has just been reported that a short while ago, a 
terrorist opened fire at several persons standing at the Ashdod 
Junction. Two people were wounded. One of the bystanders shot 
and killed the terrorist. Police forces and emergency medical 
teams rushed to the scene, and the wounded are currently 
receiving treatment. This was reported by our correspondents 
Yehudit Yehezqeli and Aviv Bushinsky. 
  [Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew at 0616 GMT on 7 April carries 
a related report, adding that "initial reports received by the 
defense establishment indicate that four people were apparently 
slightly wounded and are being treated at the scene" and that 
"additional terrorists may have been involved in the incident."] 

