<H4>    Al-Shiqaqi Says Attacks To Continue </H4>

<F P=102> NC0704184194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0704184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mohammad Beshkar in Beirut] </F>
  [Text] The Islamic Jihad in Palestine has announced its 
responsibility for the operation carried out by one of the 
Palestinian mujahidin this morning in the occupied city of 
Ashdod, north of the Gaza Strip. A Zionist settler was killed 
and four others were wounded in the attack. A statement by the 
movement obtained by our radio says: 'Ali al-'Amawi, an Islamic 
Jihad member from the al-Shati' camp in Gaza, acting alone, 
attacked a group of armed Zionist settlers in Ashdod this 
morning, killing one and seriously wounding four others. The 
mujahid was martyred by Israeli occupation forces' gunfire 
during the attack. 
  In a telephone contact with him a short time ago, Dr. Fathi 
al- Shiqaqi, secretary general of the Islamic Jihad in 
Palestine, stressed the continuation of jihad and military 
operations against the occupation forces and the Zionist 
settlers. He condemned UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
and the president of the Security Council for rushing to condemn 
the martyrdom-seeking operation in 'Afula, north of occupied 
Palestine, yesterday. He said this proves that the United 
Nations and the Security Council are controlled by the American 
will. Asked about the Islamic Jihad in Palestine's operation 
today, he said: 
  [Begin al-Shiqaqi recording] The operations will continue. 
They reflect our people's protest against and rejection of the 
alleged and [word indistinct] peace agreement between the PLO 
and the Israelis. They stress that our people's option is to 
continue jihad and fight despite all attempts by the United 
States, the Zionist enemy, and the official Palestinian side to 
implement the Oslo agreement, which, again, I stress, makes 
peace for no one but gives another reason for war. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

