<H3> <TI>   Police Capture Fugitive Kakh Leader Barukh Marzel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Capture Fugitive Kakh Leader Barukh Marzel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0304043294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 3 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0304043294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Barukh Marzel, who was sought by the police for 
three weeks, was arrested a short while ago in the settlement of 
Bney Sever, south of Qiryat Arba'. 
  Our police affairs correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that 
detectives from the National Unit for Serious Crimes 
Investigations, policemen from the Judaea Region, and a Border 
Police contingent captured Barukh Marzel at his hideout. He is 
currentlty being interrogated at the Petah Tiqva offices of the 
Natioanl Unit for Serious Crimes Investigations. 

</TEXT>

