<H3> <TI>   Fatah Member Killed While Assembling Bomb </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Member Killed While Assembling Bomb </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0204193794 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0204193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Excerpts] A Fatah member from Khan Yunus was killed this 
evening as he was assembling a bomb in the Khan Yunus refugee 
camp. The victim is Khalid Halabi, who spent eight years in an 
Israeli prison because of his Fatah membership. His body was 
snatched away from the hospital. 
  Our correspondent Shlomi Eldar adds that shots were fired 
this evening at an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] lookout position 
in al-Shaykh Radwan. Nobody was hurt. The Fatah Hawks claimed 
responsibility for this attempted terrorist attack. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1900 GMT on 2 April 
adds: [passage omitted] "A firebomb was thrown this evening at 
an Israeli car in the 'Aqabat Jabr refugee camp on the outskirts 
of Jericho. Nobody was hurt and no damage was caused. The 
driver reported the incident and drove away. An IDF unit 
arrived on the scene and found the firebomb's remnants as well 
as empty cartridges. Shortly afterward, an Arab suffering 
serious wounds arrived in a hospital in the area. The security 
forces are checking whether the man was the one who threw the 
firebomb and was wounded by shots fired by passengers aboard the 
Israeli car."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

