<F P=101> YEMEN </F>
<H3> <TI>   INA Report: Saudi Behind Kidnapping of Two Chinese `Experts' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    INA Report: Saudi Behind Kidnapping of Two Chinese `Experts' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0304152594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1440 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0304152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 3 Apr (INA)--Yemeni gunmen today kidnapped 
two members of a Chinese team that is working on the 
Jihanah-Ma'rib road project, 49 km northeast of the Yemeni 
capital, Sanaa. 
  To free the two Chinese experts, the kidnappers are 
demanding 
that work on the road, which extends over 76 km along the Saudi- 
Yemeni border, be stopped. The project was started in 1991. 
  On 12 February, Yemeni gunmen kidnapped three Chinese 
experts 
working on the same project. The experts were released on 21 
February. 
  Informed Yemeni sources have indicated that the Saudi regime 
is behind the kidnapping, and that this regime seeks to obstruct 
the project, which, once completed, would allow the Yemeni 
authorities to control smuggling, curb acts of economic 
sabotage, and check the Saudi regime's ambition to expand into 
Yemeni territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

