<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   2 April 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> YEMEN </F>
<H3> <TI>   GPC Official Assassinated in Ta'izz 1 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GPC Official Assassinated in Ta'izz 1 April </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0204101294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0912 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0204101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 2 Apr (INA)--Muhammad Humud al-Warifi, member 
of Yemen's General People's Congress [GPC], has been shot dead 
in Ta'izz Governorate, south of Sanaa. 
  The GPC, which is led by Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, said in a statement today that GPC member Muhammad Humud 
al-Warifi, 35, the head of the GPC's second district branch in 
Ta'izz, was assassinated by unidentified gunmen in Ta'izz at 
noon yesterday. 
  It is noteworthy that this is the second assassination 
incident within one week targeting members of the two ruling 
partners, the GPC and the Yemeni Socialist Party, which 
announced on Sunday that one of its members, a military officer, 
was killed in Sanaa, the capital. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

