<H3> <TI>   Public Security Unit Said Behind Yeoryiadhis Killing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Public Security Unit Said Behind Yeoryiadhis Killing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0504155294 Istanbul OZGUR GUNDEM in Turkish 3 Apr 94 pp 1, 
11 </F>

<F P=103> NC0504155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul OZGUR GUNDEM </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It is being claimed that Cypriot Theofilos 
Yeoryiadhis, who was a friend of the Kurds, was murdered by the 
Public Security Unit (KGB) [Kamu Guvenligi Birimi], which is 
attached to the Presidency of the General Staff. [see 28 March 
Terrorism Report] 
  A high-ranking officer serving in north Cyprus claimed that 
the assassination of Yeoryiadhis, the head of the Committee for 
Solidarity With Kurdistan and of the Greek Cypriot information 
department, was planned by the Public Security Unit (KGB) 
attached to the Presidency of the General Staff. 
  Claiming that the General Staff has formed a new team in 
north Cyprus from officers who received antiterrorism and 
psychological warfare training in the United States and Israel, 
the officer asserted that the assassination of Yeoryiadhis in 
south Cyprus marked the implementation of a strategy developed 
over the past two years. [passage omitted] 
<H5>  KGB Was Established in January </H5>
  The Public Security Unit (KGB), which was established last 
January, is working under the National Security Council on 
issues relating to "the PKK and major social developments." The 
KGB, which is composed of seven people, is also tasked to ensure 
coordination between MIT, the General Directorate of Security, 
and the Foreign Ministry. 

</TEXT>

