<F P=106> [DDP report: "FOCUS Insists: Slip-Ups Occurred in Bad </F>
Kleinen"] 
  [Excerpt] Munich -- Despite official denials, slip-ups 
are believed to have occurred during the antiterrorism operation 
in Bad Kleinen, which led to the escape of four members of the 
Red Army Faction [RAF]. This was confirmed yesterday by the 
news magazine FOCUS. The magazine quotes notes and reports by 
analysts of the Federal Office of Criminal Investigation [BKA]. 
  In December 1993, the BKA prepared a leaflet showing a man 
and a woman. Moreover, the magazine quotes the following note: 
"During a later evaluation of the videotapes of the operation 
in Bad Kleinen, a specialist of BKA section 21, which is 
responsible for terrorism, discovered that the man might be one 
and the same as the man who is believed to have been involved in 
the attack on former Trust Agency head Rohwedder." An analyst 
stated that he is "100 percent sure" that the unknown man 
participated in the attack, the magazine reports. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

