</HEADER>

<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   18 April 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> PERU </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Agreement With Shining Path </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peace Agreement With Shining Path </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Confusion,' Suspicion </H4>

<F P=102> PY1804204894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1819 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1804204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 18 Apr (EFE) -- The peace proposal made by 
the Shining Path [SL] on 16 April over a Lima television channel 
has created some confusion and lead to some speculation 
regarding President Alberto Fujimori's relationship with the SL 
leadership, which may end in amnesty for all terrorists. 
  The proposal made by one of the hooded terrorists who 
appears 
on the video sent to several television channels points out the 
need for a peace agreement, under the condition that the 
terrorists suspend their attacks and the government its 
antiterrorist struggle. 
  During the political program "En Directo" 
[Straightforwardly], broadcast on 17 April in the evening, 
journalist Fernando Rospigliosi disclosed that President 
Fujimori on 15 April visited the Yanamayo prison where several 
terrorists, among them Osman Morote, who is the second or third 
highest SL leader, are held under arrest. 
  According to Rospigliosi, Morote, with a smile on his face, 
delivered a gift to the president, but as he could not get it 
through the bars the cell door was opened and Fujimori entered 
it, where he exchanged brief comments with Morote. 
  This year Fujimori also shook hands with SL leader Edmundo 
Cox in the prison where he is being held, and it is said that 
Fujimori sent [Abimael] Guzman a letter on his birthday in 
December, although that information was denied at the time. 
  According to Rospigliosi, these facts "are worrisome" and 
may 
end up with Fujimori, if he runs for reelection in 1995 and 
wins, pardoning the terrorists. 
  However, recently Fujimori asserted that no sentence against 
terrorists, whether they belong to the SL or the Tupac Amaru 
Revolutionary Movement (MRTA), will be reviewed. 
  The fact is that the SL leaders under arrest, since Abimael 
Guzman sent his first two letters to Fujimori in September and 
October 1993 proposing peace, smile and treat the chief of state 
respectfully. 
  There are also versions stating that the terrorists' 
attitude 
is merely a SL maneuver because in truth they continue their 
attacks, headed by Oscar Ramirez (aka Feliciano) and a group of 
women that have not paid heed to Guzman's order to halt acts of 
violence. 
  In the opinion of terrorism expert Carlos Chipoco, the SL 
wants peace because "it is very weak and virtually defeated from 
the military viewpoint." 
  According to the monthly PERU-PAZ, since Guzman was arrested 
on 12 September 1992, the SL "has been incapable of recovering 
its guerrilla action power" it had before the leader was 
arrested. 
  The latest data reveals that during the first quarter of 
1994, 111 people died as a result of political violence compared 
to 573 for the same period in 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

