<H3> <TI>   Security Services Disband `Terrorist Network' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Services Disband `Terrorist Network' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304211494 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A statement by the security services today said that 
on the basis of information, a terrorist network involved in an 
attempt to sabotage El Hadjar [steel] complex has been 
disbanded. The information led to the siege of a bakery in 
Guemar, the province of El Oued, the killing of four terrorists, 
the arrest of another six, and the seizure of a quantity of arms. 
  Investigations led to the arrest of 29 people in (Oued Souf) 
and 14 in Annaba, and the killing of 14 terrorists in a hideout 
in (Oued El Annab) and two terrorists in (Djebel Gamgam) in the 
province of Tebessa, where five gendarmes were killed in an 
exchange of fire. This terrorist network was composed of people 
from Guemar and Oued Souf. Some of them were lying in wait at 
El Hadjar complex and had started to execute a plan to 
assassinate members of the security and sabotagie El Hadjar 
complex. This group was active under the leadership of the 
so-called (Basi Taher) who is a baker in the Guemar municipality. 

</TEXT>

