<H3> <TI>   Explosion in South Cairo; No Casualties Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion in South Cairo; No Casualties Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1504193094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1910 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1504193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 15 Apr (MENA) -- A crude home-made device 
exploded tonight in front of building No. 3 in Madinat al-Ikha' 
in [Cairo's southern] neighborhood of al-Ma'adi. There were no 
damages, injuries, or casualties. 
  This was stated by an Interior Ministry security source 
which 
said that the explosion happened at 1830 today and that the 
Cairo Security Directorate officials and the criminal laboratory 
experts immediately went to the site. It added that the search 
for the culprits is under way and that the public prosecution 
office has been notified so as to start its investigation. 

</TEXT>

