<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes in Tehran 19 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Explodes in Tehran 19 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Security Sources Claim Iraqi Saboteurs </H4>

<F P=102> LD1904102794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The explosion of a bomb in the vicinity of Tehran's 
Sa'di Avenue caused some damage today. According to the Central 
News Unit, the bomb was apparently planted inside a car that was 
parked under Sa'di Bridge. As a result of the explosion, one 
vehicle was destroyed, a number of passing vehicles suffered 
some damage, and the windows of several shops were broken. 
  Fortunately, the incident did not cause any deaths. 
According to witnesses, a number of passers by were injured in 
the incident. 
  Reliable security sources have announced: The Iraqi regime 
has recently sent four persons to Iran plant bombs for the 
purpose of sabotage, and today's explosion was caused by these 
same saboteurs. 

</TEXT>

