<H3> <TI>   `Serious Information' Offered to U.S. on New York Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Serious Information' Offered to U.S. on New York Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1204184894 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1807 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1204184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official spokesman has stated the following: 
  The Iraqi intelligence services have acquired documented and 
serious information regarding the incident of the explosion at 
the World Trade Center in New York. 
  This information raises many suspicions about the parties 
that took part in or were behind the incident. 
  The competent Iraqi authorities are willing to cooperate 
with 
the United States to learn the facts as they exist. We hope 
that the U.S. side that handles this will be impartial. It is 
preferable that this should be done with the knowledge of the 
U.S. Congress or under its supervision. 

</TEXT>

