<H3> <TI>   Bomb Blast in Hadera </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Blast in Hadera </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Initial Report </H4>

<F P=102> TA1304070994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0653 GMT 13 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1304070994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Here is a report just in: There was an 
explosion on a bus in the Hadera central bus station. Our 
correspondent Yo'av Aviv is on the line with more details: 
  The explosion occurred in the back part of the bus, near the 
rear exit door. We know that there were fatalities -- apparently 
one or two people were killed in the blast. I must stress that 
this is an initial report, and the details may not be final. 
There are wounded too, and they are being evacuated by 
ambulances to the Hilel Yafe Hospital in Hadera. 
  Police have cordoned off the area and have already collected 
eye witnesses' testimonies about Arabs they had seen on that 
bus. Those who placed the explosive charge may have gotten off 
earlier. Searches are in progress. 
  To repeat, an explosive charge went off aboard bus No. 820 
from 'Afula to Tel Aviv. The charge went off when the bus got 
to Hadera. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

