<H4>    Six Killed, Some 25 Wounded </H4>

<F P=102> TA1304082394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0755 GMT 13 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1304082394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Six were killed and about 25 wounded, mostly 
lightly, in an explosion inside a bus during a boarding interval 
in the Hadera central bus station. The No. 820 bus was on its 
way from 'Afula to Tel Aviv. 
  It is believed that Arabs, who boarded the bus at one of the 
stops, left the bomb on the bus. Another theory says the 
perpetrator was a suicide terrorist. [passage omitted] 
  Our correspondent Yo'av Aviv adds that there has been a 
second explosion on the bus, this time apparently a planned 
blast activated by bomb disposal experts, who found another 
bomb. The Hadera central bus station has been closed off, and 
local inhabitants are staging a demonstration nearby, calling 
out anti-Arab slogans. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

