BFN 

  [Text] Three katyusha rockets mounted and ready to be 
launched at Israel were found in south Lebanon this morning. 
The rockets were found and detonated at the site by UN soldiers 
in south Lebanon. 
  Our correspondent Yo'av Aviv reports that several katyusha 
rockets were fired on the security zone at midday. They fell 
inside the south Lebanese security zone, near the Israeli 
border. Qiryat Shemona and confrontation line residents were 
ordered into shelters. 
  Major General Yitzhaq Mordekhay, the Northern Command 
commander, said the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] will not permit 
Hizballah to bring about an escalation in the situation in south 
Lebanon. 

