<H3> <TI>   Special Force To Combat `Nuclear Terrorism' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Special Force To Combat `Nuclear Terrorism' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904170294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1328 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The currently reorganized special force Vympel will 
combat nuclear terrorism, Commander of the Russian Interior 
Troops, Colonel General Anatoliy Kulikov announced on Tuesday. 
  He said that Vympel would be directly controlled by the 
interior minister. 
  He also pointed out that the tactics of the interior troops 
guarding nuclear power plants and nuclear defense facilities 
have become outdated in as they were mostly oriented against 
individual terrorists, not organized criminals. The interior 
troops also lack armored equipment and special security devices, 
said Kulikov. There are plans to equip servicemen with gas 
weapons, he stated. 
  He also complained that the interior troops were 49 percent 
understaffed. 

</TEXT>

