<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explosions Damage Two Banks, No Injuries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Explosions Damage Two Banks, No Injuries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1204150294 Brussels BELGA Database in French 1212 GMT 12 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BR1204150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA Database </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by JCH/RHR: "Two Bomb Attacks Against Banks in </F>
Luxembourg"] 
  [Text] Luxembourg, 12 Apr (BELGA) -- During the night from 
Monday to Tuesday, two banks in the Grand-Duchy of Luxembourg 
were damaged by explosions, the legal authorities revealed 
Tuesday. Nobody was injured. 
  At approximately 0040 GMT on Tuesday morning, an explosive 
charge went off in front of the entrance to the Caisse Rurale in 
Bous, which is situated approximately 12 km from the capital, 
near the German-Luxembourg border. One hour later, at 
approximately 0200 GMT, a second explosive charge went off 
outside the entrance to a branch of the Caisse d'Epargne de 
l'Etat in Bridel, in the center of the country, about 10 km away 
from Luxembourg. 
  The door and a few windows were blown to pieces. Nobody was 
injured. No witnesses noticed whether there had been one or 
more terrorists at the site of the explosions. The explosives 
used were stolen from a quarry one week ago. 
  Nobody has claimed responsibility for the attacks. The 
special branch of the gendarmerie and the crime squad are 
conducting an inquiry. 

</TEXT>

