<F P=103> TA1504070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpts] Alpaslan Pehlivanli, Motherland Party [ANAP] 
Central Decision-Making and Executive Council member and former 
Ankara deputy, has been killed in an armed attack near 
Kirikkale's Keskin District. According to information obtained 
by a Turkish Radio and Television correspondent from Kirikkale 
Governor Sahabettin Harput, three shots were fired from the 
passing car at Pehlivanli who was driving from Keskin to 
Kirikkale. Pehlivanli was seriously injured in the head and he 
died on the way to the hospital. Three other persons who were 
in the car with him did not sustain any injuries in the attack. 
It is reported that the car from which the shots were fired had 
a fake license plate and that there were four persons in it. 
Operations are continuing to capture the assailants. [passage 
omitted on Pehlivanli's curriculum vitae] 
  ANAP leader Mesut Yilmaz went to Kirikkale following the 
incident. He went to the hospital where Pehlivanli was taken 
and was briefed on the incident by Harput and other officials. 
In a statement at the hospital, Yilmaz said that there is a 
high possibility that it is a political murder and that the 
authorities concerned are continuing the investigation. Yilmaz 
said: The incident is very distressing for us. We are 
heartbroken. I extend my condolences to the people of Kirikkale 
and ANAP circles. 

</TEXT>

