<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cross-Border Operation Against PKK In Northern Iraq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cross-Border Operation Against PKK In Northern Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1404121094 Istanbul MILLIYET in Turkish 14 Apr 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> NC1404121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul MILLIYET </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Turkish ground and air force units and Kurdish 
peshmergas affiliated with Democratic Party of Kurdistan leader 
Mas'ud Barzani have launched a major operation against the 
Kurdish Workers Party [PKK] militants in northern Iraq. Some 
40,000 troops and 3,000 commandos affiliated with the commando 
brigade on Hakkari Mountain have penetrated 5 km into northern 
Iraq. The joint cross-border operation, which was launched by 
the Turkish military forces on Turkey's border and the peshmerga 
units in northern Iraq, is supported by several Turkish military 
aircraft and Cobra and Sikorsky helicopters. 
  Several military aircraft, which took off from the 2d 
Tactical Air Base in Diyarbakir and the Erhac Air Base in 
Malatya, have bombed the Besta Valley and the heights of the 
Cudi, Gabbar, Herekol, Namaz, and Kupeli Mountains. Several 
Super Cobra helicopters joined the operation at about noon 
yesterday. 
  Elsewhere, a private vehicle was destroyed by a PKK mine 
near 
Emekciler village in Siirt at about 1600 yesterday. The 
vehicle's driver and four village guards, who were his 
passengers, were killed in the incident. 
  Three soldiers were martyred and three others were wounded 
in 
a clash between the security forces and a group of terrorists 
near the Tur farming settlement near the village of Islam in 
Diyarbakir's Kulp district yesterday. A terrorist was also 
killed in the clash. 
  The security forces killed four PKK terrorists in the rural 
areas of Igdir's Halfeli village, two terrorists in the forest 
areas of Kars' Sarikamis district, and one terrorist in the 
rural areas of Hakkari's Yuksekova district. 
  A group of terrorists attacked the Garzan-Besiri oil 
pipeline 
at about 2200 the night before last. The pipeline is operated 
by the Turkish Petroleum Corporation's regional directorate in 
Batman. No one was killed in the incident. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

