<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explosion Kills Six in Nakhon Si Thammarat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Explosion Kills Six in Nakhon Si Thammarat </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Railway Station Targetted </H4>

<F P=102> BK2304081494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Public Relations Department correspondent 
reported from Nakhon Si Thammarat Province that a bomb exploded 
at the railway station in Nakhon Si Thammarat at about noon. 
The motive of the explosion is unknown. Six persons were 
killed instantly and several were injured. Second Lieutenant 
Thanaphong Chakkaphak, Nakhon Si Thammarat deputy governor, and 
police officials went to the scene to investigate the incident. 
Those injured were rushed to the Maharat Hospital of Nakhon Si 
Thammarat for treatment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

