<F P=101> ARGENTINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes at Army Officer's Home </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Explodes at Army Officer's Home </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1904220994 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2104 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1904220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cordoba, 19 Apr (NA) -- A low-intensity explosive 
device exploded at the home of an Army official who, according 
to what neighbors reported, had been commissioned to Artillery 
Group No. 161 in Zapala, Neuquen Province. 
  Even though the reports that First Lieutenant Daniel Vega, a 
physician, had been commissioned to that garrison were not 
officially confirmed, they were not denied by military 
authorities either. 
  According to what was made public by Cordoba Province 
Police, 
the explosive device went off at around 0200 local time and 
caused only minor damage and no injuries. 
  The explosion only caused some damage to the door of the 
house located at 112 Jacinto Rios Street in the General Paz 
district, where Vega and his wife live. 

</TEXT>

