<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish at 1737 
GMT on 18 April reports that the Venezuelan Armed Forces and the 
Technical Judicial Police are investigating an attack by 
unidentified individuals on the Vicente Landaeta Gil military 
air base west of Barquisimeto. The men tried to break into the 
base's radar site. In the ensuing shooting, two soldiers were 
wounded, one of them badly. It has not yet been determined 
whether the attack was perpetrated by common criminals or was 
politically motivated. 

