<H4>    Coordination Meetings </H4>

<F P=102> TA2304193394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 23 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2304193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The heads of most terror organizations in the Gaza 
Strip have met in Gaza over the last two days. The meetings 
included Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement], Islamic Jihad, and 
rejectionist organizations members. The meetings were held to 
prepare for the autonomy period. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan 
reports the meetings were initiated by PLO officials in the Gaza 
Strip. The participants discussed cooperation possibilities 
between the various organizations, with the view of establishing 
a civilian and security cooperation apparatus after the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] withdraws from the area. The meetings 
were held against the background of an agreement reached 
yesterday between 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam, Hamas' military arm, 
and the Fatah Hawks on putting an end to acts of revenge against 
collaborators and stopping the strikes. 

</TEXT>

