<H3> <TI>   Hamas Continues Agressive Stance Toward Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Continues Agressive Stance Toward Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leaflet Says Struggle To Go On Until Occupation Ends </H4>

<F P=102> TA2104152094 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 21 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> TA2104152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Pinhas 'Inbari] </F>
  [Text] The 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam squads yesterday 
clarified for the first time that they will stop fighting Israel 
when it withdraws from the Gaza Strip and the West Bank. This 
is the first time an 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam leaflet has featured 
such a statement. 
  The belligerent leaflet announces that Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] is not intimidated by arrests. On the 
contrary, the recent spate of arrests will inspire it to 
escalate its struggle. The leaflet warns Shin Bet officers that 
their fate will be similar to that of No'am Kohen and Hayim 
Nahmani. 
  The leaflet goes on to point out, however, that the movement 
will pursue its war on "terrorists Rabin and Baraq" as long as 
even a single Israeli soldier remains in the West Bank and Gaza. 
Until now, the leaflets of the military branch of Hamas have 
always referred to an all-out war, and not to a war until the 
end of occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

