<H3> <TI>   Hamas Continues Agressive Stance Toward Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Continues Agressive Stance Toward Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Stresses `Escalation' </H4>

<F P=102> JN2204093294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0858 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2204093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 22 Apr (INA) -- The Political Bureau of the 
Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas, has stressed the continued 
escalation of military operations against the Zionist occupation 
forces as long as occupation exists on Palestinian territory. 
  In a statement published in Sanaa yesterday, Hamas urged the 
unconditional withdrawal of the Zionist forces from the West 
Bank, Gaza Strip, and Jerusalem as well as the removal of the 
settlements, the evacuation of the settlers from the West Bank, 
Gaza Strip, and Jerusalem and the holding of free legislative 
elections for the Palestinian people inside and outside the 
occupied territories. 

</TEXT>

