<H3> <TI>   Three Reported Injured in Cairo Bomb Blast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three Reported Injured in Cairo Bomb Blast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2304102594 Paris AFP in English 0943 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2304102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, April 23 (AFP) -- Three people were injured 
Saturday when a bomb exploded in an empty house in northern 
Cairo believed to be used as an arms store by Islamic militants, 
security officials said. 
  The blast, in the densely-populated al-Matariyah district, 
injured three passers-by. 
  Police were questioning an Islamic militant in connection 
with the incident. 
  Two Islamic militants were injured Thursday when five 
explosive devices they were planning to use in attacks 
accidentally blew up in a shop in the 'Ayn Shams district of 
Cairo. 
  The blast badly damaged the front of the shop, which was 
owned by one of the injured, a chemist. His cousin was also 
hurt. 
  The outlawed Islamic group al-Jama'ah al-Islamiyah has been 
waging a violent two-year campaign to topple Egypt's secular 
government in which more than 360 people have died. 

</TEXT>

