<H3> <TI>   Attempt on Minister's Life Referred to Military Judiciary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attempt on Minister's Life Referred to Military Judiciary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2204102794 Cairo AL-AHRAM in Arabic 18 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2204102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHRAM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A republican decree was issued yesterday, referring 
case No. 574 for the year 1993 to the military judiciary. 
Al-Jihad organization members involved in the case are accused 
of the attempted assassination of Interior Minister Hasan 
al-Alfi, the assassination of a car showroom owner in Shibin 
al-Qanatir, and of detonating a bomb in the al-Jazirah youth 
center. 
  Judicial sources have said that the case files will be 
handed 
to the military prosecution in the next few hours to begin 
interrogating the apprehended defendants, mainly Muhammad 
'Abd-al- 'Alim Khalifah and Muhammad Rashad. The defendants 
will face charges for murder, attempted murder, and possession 
of weapons, bombs and ammunition. They face a punishment that 
can be anything from death, life with hard labor, to 
imprisonment. 

</TEXT>

