<H3> <TI>   Security Source Denies Terrorists Raising Funds in Aswan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Source Denies Terrorists Raising Funds in Aswan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104035794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2035 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104035794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aswan, 20 Apr (MENA) -- A responsible security 
source in the Aswan Security Directorate has denied a report 
published recently by an opposition paper claiming that a group 
calling itself Jama'at al-Intiqam [The Revenge Group] in the 
Aswan Governorate has raised 250,000 pounds from the 
governorate's inhabitants to finance retaliatory operations 
against the police agencies in revenge for the death of eight 
members of the group in the Markaz Idfu. 
  The security source stressed that the security organs in the 
governorate are on full alert to confront any terrorist actions 
and abort them immediately. 
  It added that there are no moves to raise funds in the Aswan 
Governorate for this or any other purpose. It stressed that 
security in the governorate is stable following the recent 
security blows dealt by the security organs to the extremist 
terrorist elements. 

