<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Railway Officials Find Time Bomb, Detain Georgians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104152194 Baku TURAN in English 0947 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, April 19, (TURAN) -- Azerbaijan's security 
agencies have prevented a new tragedy on Azeri railway from 
taking place. TURAN was told that this most recent attempted act 
of terrorism was planned for today in wagon number 5 along the 
Baku-Moscow route. 
  During an inspection of wagons and passengers' belongings 
security employees found a cardbord box with a large timing 
devise. 
  The timing devise weighed 13 kilos and consisted of 65 
pieces 
of dynamite placed in soap weighing 200 grammes each. The box 
belonged to five Georgian citizens. Presently they are being 
detained by Azeri security bodies. 

</TEXT>

