<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Operations Against PKK Since January </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister on Operations Against PKK Since January </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404111994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has declared that 
during operations conducted against the terrorist PKK [Workers 
Party of Kurdistan] organization since the beginning of 1994, 
1,037 terrorists were killed, 871 of whom were killed in the 
state of emergency region. During the same period, a total of 
1,976 terrorists were captured. Of these 865 terrorists were 
caught in the state of emergency region. Mentese added that 88 
terrorists surrendered to the security forces in the same period. 
  In a statement he issued today, the interior minister 
reported that a group of militants -- comprised of approximately 
4,500 persons -- was neutralized as a result of intelligence 
work and weakening within the organization. Mentese declared 
that as a result of coordinated operations conducted by the 
Turkish Armed Forces and the security forces, the terrorist 
organization sustained significant loss of logistic support and 
militants. In northern Iraq, Mentese reported, 79 terrorists 
were killed and two were captured. 
  Pointing out that nothing can be achieved through terrorism, 
Mentese reiterated his call on the youth, who are deceived by 
the PKK, to surrender as soon as possible and benefit from the 
repentance law. 

</TEXT>

